# Versioning, changelog, and file manifest

## Repository

- **GitHub:** `https://github.com/dpiersol/call-pat-prototype` (also set on root `package.json` as `repository.url` for tooling).
- When documenting releases or builds, **always include this URL** next to the version string.

## Version format `vM.m.T` (root `package.json` `version`, no `v` prefix in JSON)

| Segment | Meaning |
|--------|---------|
| **M** | **Development milestone** — bump only when the product milestone changes (major phase). |
| **m** | **Iterations within the milestone** — after every **successful** full workspace `npm run build`, the post-build step records the new version in `CHANGELOG.md` and bumps **m** (middle segment), resetting **T** to `0`. |
| **T** | **Unit test iterations** — bump with `npm run version:test-iteration` (or equivalent) when completing a deliberate test iteration (e.g. new suite, fix wave). Document the change in `CHANGELOG.md`. |

Format examples: `1.0.0`, `1.3.0`, `1.3.2` (not `v1.0.0` inside `package.json`; use `v` prefix in changelog headings only if desired for readability — project uses `## vM.m.T` in `CHANGELOG.md`).

## After every build

1. Root `npm run build` must run `scripts/record-build.mjs` so **`CHANGELOG.md`** gains a dated entry with **version** and **repository URL**.
2. Do not skip the changelog when the build is the canonical “green” build for a change set.
3. Optional: set `BUILD_NOTE="short summary"` for a one-line note in that changelog entry.

## File manifest

- When **creating** or **renaming** meaningful source files, scripts, or config, add or update a row in **`docs/FILE_MANIFEST.md`**: **path**, **purpose** (one line), **who uses it** (app, script, CI, humans).
- Prefer updating the manifest in the **same commit** as the new file.

## Milestone bumps (M)

- Bumping **M** is manual: edit root `package.json` `version`, add a `CHANGELOG.md` section explaining the new milestone, and align any external dashboards.
